  "prompt": "Isn't money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or other crimes) appear legitimate by funneling it through a series of transactions or businesses. The goal is to disguise the illicit origin of the funds so they can be used without attracting suspicion from law enforcement or tax authorities.\n\nMost countries have strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering, and financial institutions are required to implement measures to detect and report suspicious activities. Penalties for money laundering can include significant fines, asset seizure, and imprisonment. International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) work to set global standards and promote effective enforcement of anti-money laundering (AML) laws.",
